{
  "info": {
    "name": "Student Practice API Collection",
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "description": "A complete REST API collection for Postman practice. Covers Authentication (Register/Login/Logout), Product CRUD, User Profile, and Order Management. Base URL uses a variable — set {{base_url}} in your environment.\n\n📌 HOW TO USE:\n1. Import this collection in Postman\n2. Create an Environment and add variable: base_url = https://dummyjson.com\n3. After login, copy the token and set {{token}} in your environment\n4. Practice all endpoints!\n\n🔑 Auth endpoints don't need a token. All others require Bearer Token.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "https://dummyjson.com",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Base URL of the API. Change this in your Postman Environment."
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "JWT Token received after login. Set this after calling the Login endpoint."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "🔐 Auth",
      "description": "Authentication endpoints — Register, Login, Logout, and Get Current User.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register User",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/users/add",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["users", "add"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"John\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n  \"age\": 22,\n  \"email\": \"johndoe@example.com\",\n  \"username\": \"johndoe\",\n  \"password\": \"johndoe123\",\n  \"phone\": \"+91-9876543210\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "📝 **Register a new user.**\n\nMethod: POST\nBody: JSON with user details.\n\n✅ Expected Response: 201 Created with user object.\n\n💡 Practice: Try registering with missing fields and observe validation errors."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (jsonData.token) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"token\", jsonData.token);",
                  "    console.log(\"Token saved to environment!\");",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"emilys\",\n  \"password\": \"emilyspass\",\n  \"expiresInMins\": 30\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "🔑 **Login with username and password.**\n\nMethod: POST\nBody: JSON with credentials.\n\n✅ Expected Response: 200 OK with JWT token.\n\n💡 The test script automatically saves the token to your environment variable `{{token}}`.\n\n📌 Default test credentials: username=emilys, password=emilyspass"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Current User (Me)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{token}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "me"]
            },
            "description": "👤 **Get the currently logged-in user's profile.**\n\nMethod: GET\nAuth: Bearer Token required.\n\n✅ Expected Response: 200 OK with user data.\n\n💡 Practice: Call this WITHOUT the token and see the 401 Unauthorized error."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Auth Token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/refresh",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "refresh"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refreshToken\": \"{{token}}\",\n  \"expiresInMins\": 30\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "🔄 **Refresh your authentication token.**\n\nMethod: POST\nBody: JSON with the existing refresh token.\n\n✅ Expected Response: 200 OK with a new token.\n\n💡 In real apps, tokens expire and need refreshing. This endpoint simulates that."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
